# Copy to `.env` and fill in. `.env` is git-ignored — never commit a real token.
#
# GitHub Personal Access Token used by the GitHub MCP tool (read-only) and the
# custom draft-PR / workflow-dispatch write tools.
#   - Fine-grained PAT (recommended) scopes: Contents (RW), Pull requests (RW),
#     Actions (RW) on your fork.
#   - Must be SAML-SSO-authorized for the `Azure` org if targeting upstream.
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your_token_here

# owner/name the agent reads and opens (draft) PRs against. Point at your fork.
GITHUB_REPO=haolingdong-msft/azure-sdk-tools

# --- Azure DevOps (workflow step 3: trigger the code-quality pipeline 8178) ---
# One of the following. Simplest is an Azure DevOps PAT (Build: Read & execute).
ADO_PAT=your_azure_devops_pat_here
# Or a pre-minted AAD bearer token for the ADO resource (499b84ac-...):
# ADO_TOKEN=eyJ...
# Or (recommended for ONLINE/hosted runs) read the bearer token from Key Vault.
# The container's managed identity needs Key Vault 'get' on the 'ado-token' secret,
# which an out-of-band job (qa-bot AdoTokenRefresh timer function) keeps fresh.
# Override the secret name with ADO_TOKEN_SECRET_NAME (default 'ado-token').
# ADO_TOKEN_KEYVAULT_URL=https://kv-haoling-hackathon.vault.azure.net/
# Or set none of the above and rely on `az login` / managed identity (needs ADO org membership).

# --- Foundry Toolbox (WorkIQ) — read internal / SharePoint docs online ---
# Lets the agent read a PRIVATE SharePoint/OneDrive Excel (user telemetry) online,
# instead of downloading it. Auth uses the ambient identity (az login / managed
# identity) for the https://ai.azure.com/.default scope — grant that identity access
# to the toolbox and the SharePoint content it reads.
# Either set the full toolbox MCP URL:
# FOUNDRY_TOOLBOX_MCP_URL=https://foundry-haoling-eus2.services.ai.azure.com/api/projects/proj-default/toolboxes/read-internal-docs/mcp?api-version=v1
# Or let it be built from AI_FOUNDRY_PROJECT_ENDPOINT + the toolbox name (+ optional version):
# FOUNDRY_TOOLBOX_NAME=read-internal-docs
# FOUNDRY_TOOLBOX_VERSION=1
# Fallback for reading a private SharePoint Excel WITHOUT the toolbox: a Microsoft Graph
# token that carries Files.Read.All / Sites.Read.All (e.g. from Graph Explorer or
# Connect-MgGraph). A plain `az login` identity usually lacks these scopes.
# GRAPH_TOKEN=eyJ...

# --- Workflow inputs (workflow.py) ---
# Optional Excel of real user prompts (WorkIQ export) the agent clusters into
# common use cases in step 1. Local path OR a direct-download URL. Private
# SharePoint/OneDrive *sharing* links are auth-gated — download and use a path.
# PROMPTS_EXCEL=./user-prompts.xlsx
